data.title: Herbert Scott “Herbie” Morgan (1935
data.meta_description: Born to Stanley J. Morgan of Binghamton and Rose K. (Paul H.) Gage of Cooperstown; Herbert joined the Army and was a Sergeant in the Military Police and also served as Chaplain's Assistant.  He served in Germany during the Korean War and was discharged honorably.  Herbert attended several area colleges and graduated...
